data.text: @Agt00Soul @EricRiffe @AnalyticsEqv We are always awash with Floridians...
@JamesBazan @AnalyticsEqv Their dangerousness is outsized, for sure.
@Agt00Soul @AnalyticsEqv And probably not in numbers nearly big enough to have this effect. It shows how distorted my perception is from the outsize coverage they get.
@JamesBazan @AnalyticsEqv In the county, maybe, but not the City of Asheville.
@AnalyticsEqv @Agt00Soul Funny. My 1st thought was the anti-vaxx culture there
@Agt00Soul My 2nd thought is that NYT may be smoking crack here. According to NCDHHS's most current data, the latest 7-day average for Buncombe County is 13 cases per 100K population per day.
@Agt00Soul @EricRiffe @AnalyticsEqv AND they removed the mask mandate. On the DHHS website, we stand out black in our area.

@Agt00Soul Interesting. I'll need to think on this a mite. But the first thing I can think to say is that I no longer find infection rate data meaningful. With the US now awash in at-home tests, most + and - test results now go unrecorded. But that won't explain AVL's outlier status.
